<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="273" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,1425,1589]" box="[160,409,1425,1451]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,409,1425,1451]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">External morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,1425,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Body elongate, narrow, background colour light brown or white with irregular brown, black and white punctuations in adults. Papillae smooth, found scattered on dorsum and laterals. Rhinophores present a smooth front surface, lamellar in back. Discoidal branchial leaves.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="273" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,1633,1728]" box="[160,252,1633,1659]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,1633,1728]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
All specimens at each locality were found on the bryozoans 
<taxonomicName authority="(Delle Chiaje, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Delle Chiaje" baseAuthorityYear="1822" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Amathia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis box="[864,1081,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Amathia verticillata</emphasis>
(Delle Chiaje, 1822)
</taxonomicName>
, laying their egg masses.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758444" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6758444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758444/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="274" startId="9.[160,225,1510,1533]" targetBox="[166,1149,146,1476]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,1510,1621]" pageId="9" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,251,1510,1533]" pageId="9" pageNumber="274">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Photographs of live 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1817" box="[462,594,1510,1533]" class="Gastropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="9" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="order">Nudibranchia</taxonomicName>
