<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1871" box="[967,1112,1598,1621]" class="Gastropoda" family="Dotidae" genus="Doto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="9" pageNumber="274" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pygmaea">Doto pygmaea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="275" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1155,142,237]" box="[160,300,142,168]" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,142,168]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1155,142,237]" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">
Recently reported in 
<collectingCountry box="[410,457,178,203]" name="Italy" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">Italy</collectingCountry>
and on the Mediterranean French coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Pola M &amp; Paz-Sedano S &amp; Macali A &amp; Minchin D &amp; Marchini A &amp; Vitale F &amp; Licchelli C &amp; Crocetta F" box="[955,1142,178,203]" pageId="10" pageNumber="275" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref21840" refString="Pola M, Paz-Sedano S, Macali A, Minchin D, Marchini A, Vitale F, Licchelli C, Crocetta F. 2019. What is really out there? Review of the genus Okenia Menke, 1830 (Nudibranchia: Goniodorididae) in the Mediterranean Sea with description of two new species. PLoS ONE. 14: 1 - 31. doi: 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0215037." type="journal article" year="2019">Pola et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
); Mediterranean Spanish coast: Catalonia (
<bibRefCitation author="Pola M &amp; Paz-Sedano S &amp; Macali A &amp; Minchin D &amp; Marchini A &amp; Vitale F &amp; Licchelli C &amp; Crocetta F" box="[617,791,212,237]" pageId="10" pageNumber="275" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref21840" refString="Pola M, Paz-Sedano S, Macali A, Minchin D, Marchini A, Vitale F, Licchelli C, Crocetta F. 2019. What is really out there? Review of the genus Okenia Menke, 1830 (Nudibranchia: Goniodorididae) in the Mediterranean Sea with description of two new species. PLoS ONE. 14: 1 - 31. doi: 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0215037." type="journal article" year="2019">Pola et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
; this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="275" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,297,565]" box="[160,262,297,323]" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,297,565]" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">
<bibRefCitation author="Pola M &amp; Paz-Sedano S &amp; Macali A &amp; Minchin D &amp; Marchini A &amp; Vitale F &amp; Licchelli C &amp; Crocetta F" box="[160,378,332,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="275" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref21840" refString="Pola M, Paz-Sedano S, Macali A, Minchin D, Marchini A, Vitale F, Licchelli C, Crocetta F. 2019. What is really out there? Review of the genus Okenia Menke, 1830 (Nudibranchia: Goniodorididae) in the Mediterranean Sea with description of two new species. PLoS ONE. 14: 1 - 31. doi: 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0215037." type="journal article" year="2019">Pola et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
recently confirmed the differences between this species and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smallwood, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Smallwood" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[161,568,367,392]" class="Gastropoda" family="Goniodorididae" genus="Okenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="10" pageNumber="275" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="zoobotryon">
<emphasis box="[161,328,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">O. zoobotryon</emphasis>
(Smallwood, 1910)
</taxonomicName>
, previously recorded in the Mediterranean but originally described from the Islands of 
<collectingCountry box="[659,765,402,427]" name="Bermuda" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
. Morphological analyses in that study revealed differences in the reproductive system and the gill branches between these two species. Thus, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Pola M &amp; Paz-Sedano S &amp; Macali A &amp; Minchin D &amp; Marchini A &amp; Vitale F &amp; Licchelli C &amp; Crocetta F" box="[664,888,471,496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="275" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref21840" refString="Pola M, Paz-Sedano S, Macali A, Minchin D, Marchini A, Vitale F, Licchelli C, Crocetta F. 2019. What is really out there? Review of the genus Okenia Menke, 1830 (Nudibranchia: Goniodorididae) in the Mediterranean Sea with description of two new species. PLoS ONE. 14: 1 - 31. doi: 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0215037." type="journal article" year="2019">Pola et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, previous records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smallwood" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[161,328,506,531]" class="Gastropoda" family="Goniodorididae" genus="Okenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="10" pageNumber="275" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="zoobotryon">
<emphasis box="[161,328,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">O. zoobotryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Mediterranean are misidentifications of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pola, Paz-Sedano, Macali, Minchin, Marchini, Vitale, Licchelli and Crocetta" authorityYear="2019" box="[928,1091,506,531]" class="Gastropoda" family="Goniodorididae" genus="Okenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="10" pageNumber="275" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="longiductis">
<emphasis box="[928,1091,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">O. longiductis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smallwood" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[160,321,540,565]" class="Gastropoda" family="Goniodorididae" genus="Okenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="10" pageNumber="275" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="zoobotryon">
<emphasis box="[160,321,540,565]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="275">O. zoobotryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only present in the western Atlantic.
</paragraph>
